{
  "info": {
    "name": "FuelPanda — Fleet Tracking Platform",
    "_postman_id": "fuelpanda-collection-0001",
    "description": "Postman collection for the FuelPanda fleet & delivery management API.\n\n**Base URL:** `{{base_url}}` (defaults to `http://127.0.0.1:8000`)\n**API prefix:** `/api/v1` (already baked into each request path)\n\n**Auth:** Authentication is stubbed in this build (`get_current_admin` / `get_current_driver` inject a fake identity), so **no token or header is required**. Admin routes run as admin id=1; driver routes run as driver id=1.\n\n**Quick start (happy path):**\n1. Master data → Create Location (HUB), Create Product, Create Inventory\n2. Master data → Create Driver, Create Vehicle\n3. Allocations → Create Allocation (auto-creates a SCHEDULED shift)\n4. Shifts → list to find the `shift_id`, then Start Shift\n5. Orders → Create Order against that shift + a destination location\n6. Tracking → Ingest GPS for the shift; Fleet → Status\n7. Deliveries → Complete Delivery; then End Shift\n\nThe collection variables (`location_id`, `product_id`, `driver_id`, `vehicle_id`, `shift_id`, `order_id`, `allocation_id`, `inventory_id`) default to `1` so requests are runnable immediately — update them as you create real records.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:8000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "location_id", "value": "1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "destination_id", "value": "2", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "product_id", "value": "1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "inventory_id", "value": "1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_id", "value": "1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "vehicle_id", "value": "1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "allocation_id", "value": "1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "shift_id", "value": "1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "order_id", "value": "1", "type": "string" }
  ],
